The Temple of Venus is in an area of 
the site which was already closed to visitors, while access to the 
necropolis has been sealed off following the collapse of the wall.

However, the remainder of the site remained open to tourists today, although its offices were shut.

Giancarlo Galan, the head of a parliamentary culture commission, on Sunday lamented the latest collapse at the archaeological site near Naples, while culture minister Dario Franceschini has raised concerns about the state of one of the world's most treasured archaeological sites.

