Pompeii, which was rediscovered in the 18th century, has 
been hit by a series of collapses in recent months and years which have 
sparked international outcry over the neglect of the site.

Last year, the Italian government appointed a special official to ensure that European Union and Italian funds were properly spent to repair and protect Pompeii.

Mr Franceschini, appointed last month in the new government of Prime Minister Matteo Renzi, summoned officials responsible for the site to Rome for an 'emergency meeting' on Tuesday.

